t as a Social Good Developer.</p><p>FbStart is a program from Facebook designed to help early stage mobile startups build and grow their apps. FbStart offers up to $80,000 in tools and services. In addition to these benefits, developers are eligible to receive management consulting, exclusive access to developer courses on Coursera, access to the Universal Core content management system, and social media consulting as part of FbStart\'s Social Good package.</p><p><a href=\"http://fbstart.com\" target=\"_blank\">Apply now</a></p>','Developers on Free Basics','','publish','closed','closed','','developers','','','2015-11-04 21:31:26','2015-11-04 21:31:26','',0,'http://internetorgvip.nerderylabs.com/en/?post_type=io_story&#038;p=1431/',0,'io_story','',0),(1432,1,'2015-10-23 22:49:08','2015-10-23 22:49:08','<p>Reach over 1 billion new-to-internet users across Africa, Asia, and Latin America with your information and services by joining the Free Basics Platform.</p><h3>Free Basics Incubator</h3><p>If you need technical assistance to create a website that is compatible with Free Basics, apply to the Free Basics Incubator.</p><p>Free Basics Incubator, a joint project from Facebook and the Praekelt Foundation, offers 100 social change organizations $200,000 in services and support, including technical tools, content development and management support, capacity building consulting, and leadership training. The Incubator will help you adapt your content and add it to Free Basics.</p><p><a href=\"https://jonathanmckay.typeform.com/to/QekN63\">Apply now</a></p><h3>FbStart</h3><p>If you already have a website or mobile app and are looking for opportunities to grow, apply to FbStart.</p><p>FbStart is a program from Facebook designed to help early stage mobile startups build and grow their apps. FbStart offers up to $80,000 in tools and services. In addition to these benefits, developers are eligible to receive management consulting, exclusive access to developer courses on Coursera, access to the Universal Core content management system, and social media consulting as part of FbStart\'s Social Good package.</p><p><a href=\"https://fbstart.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Apply now</a></p><h3>Contact Us</h3><p>To learn more about how to add your website to the Free Basics Platform, get in touch with our team.</p><p><a href=\"mailto:fbs@fb.com\">Contact us</a></p>','Non-Profits on Free Basics','','publish','closed','closed','','non-profits','','','2015-11-04 21:31:00','2015-11-04 21:31:00','',0,'http://internetorgvip.nerderylabs.com/en/?post_type=io_story&#038;p=1432/',0,'io_story','',0),(1434,1,'2015-10-23 23:36:30','2015-10-23 23:36:30','<p>Free Basics is available in 29 countries with the following mobile operators:</p><h4>Africa</h4><ul><li>Angola (Movicel)</li><li>Democratic Republic of the Congo (Tigo)</li><li>Egypt (Etisalat)</li><li>Ghana (Airtel)</li><li>Kenya (Airtel)</li><li>Liberia (Cellcom)</li><li>Malawi (Airtel &amp; TNM)</li><li>Mozambique (Mcel)</li><li>Rwanda (Airtel)</li><li>Senegal (Tigo)</li><li>Seychelles (Airtel) </li><li>South Africa (Cell C)</li><li>Tanzania (Tigo)</li><li>Zambia (Airtel)</li></ul><h4>Asia</h4><ul><li>Bangladesh (Robi)</li><li>Cambodia (Smart Axiata)</li><li>India (Reliance)</li><li>Indonesia (Indosat)</li><li>Maldives (Ooredoo)</li><li>Mongolia (Mobicom) </li><li>Pakistan (Telenor)</li><li>Philippines (Globe &amp; Smart)</li><li>Thailand (TrueMove)</li><li>Timor-Leste (Telkomcel) </li></ul><h4>Latin America</h4><ul><li>Bolivia (Viva)</li><li>Colombia (Tigo)</li><li>Guatemala (Tigo)</li><li>Panama (Digicel)</li><li>Peru (Entel)</li></ul><p>Free Basics will continue to expand to more countries around the world.</p>','Where we\'ve launched','','publish','closed','closed','','where-weve-launched','','','2015-11-04 19:40:09','2015-11-04 19:40:09','',0,'http://internetorgvip.nerderylabs.com/en/?post_type=io_story&#038;p=1434/',0,'io_story','',0),(1439,1,'2015-10-27 16:24:56','2015-10-27 16:24:56','','Facebook Page'