with Free Basics, apply to the Free Basics Incubator. Free Basics Incubator, a joint project from Facebook and the Praekelt Foundation, offers 100 social change organizations $200,000 in services and support, including technical tools, content development and management support, capacity building consulting, and leadership training. The Incubator will help you adapt your content and add it to Free Basics. <a href=\"https://jonathanmckay.typeform.com/to/QekN63\">Apply now</a></p><h3>FbStart</h3><p>If you already have a website or mobile app and are looking for opportunities to grow, apply to FbStart. FbStart is a program from Facebook designed to help early stage mobile startups build and grow their apps. FbStart offers up to $80,000 in tools and services. In addition to these benefits, FbStart Social Good Developers are eligible to receive management consulting, exclusive access to developer courses on Coursera, access to the Universal Core content management system, and social media consulting. <a href=\"https://fbstart.com/\">Apply now</a></p><h3>Contact Us</h3><p>To learn more about how to add your website to the Free Basics Platform, get in touch with our team. <a href=\"mailto:fbs@fb.com\">Contact us</a></p>','Non-Profits on Free Basics','','inherit','closed','closed','','1432-autosave-v1','','','2015-10-29 04:58:58','2015-10-29 04:58:58','',1432,'http://vip.local/en/blog/2015/10/29/1432-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1626,1,'2015-11-05 03:40:21','2015-11-05 03:40:21','<h1 class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Reach the next wave of internet users.</span></h1><ul class=\"ul1\"><li class=\"li1\"><span class=\"s1\">Grow your audience by providing affordable access to your services.</span></li><li class=\"li1\"><span class=\"s1\">Scale your social impact.</span></li><li class=\"li1\"><span class=\"s1\">Establish your brand </span><span class=\"s2\">early</span><span class=\"s1\"> in the fastest-growing mobile markets.</span></li></ul><p>Join the Free Basics Platform to add your website to <a href=\"/story/free-basics-from-internet-org/\">Free Basics</a>, which provides people free access to a range of basic services in markets where internet access may be less affordable.</p><p>You are already building valuable services - apps, websites, and information - that are impacting people\'s lives. But, it\'s difficult to access those not yet connected to the internet. By joining the Free Basics Platform, you can now reach the previously unconnected. </p><h3>Developers</h3><p>Reach new-to-internet users across Africa, Asia, and Latin America and make a social impact by adapting your mobile app or website for the Free Basics platform.</p><p><a href=\"/story/developers/\">Get started</a></p><h3>Non-profit Organizations</h3><p>If you are a non-profit organization or NGO with services or information that is beneficial for new-to-internet users, there are resources that can help you build and adapt your website for Free Basics.</p><p><a href=\"/story/non-profits/\">Learn more</a></p><h3>Governments</h3><p>Provide essential information to your citizens through Free Basics.</p><p><a href=\"contact-us/contact-free-basic-services/\">Contact us</a></p><h3>Success Stories</h3><p><strong><a href=\"http://m-smartbusiness.com/sa/\">SmartBusiness</a></strong>, a South African website that helps people launch and run businesses, receives 5x more daily searches since joining the Free Basics Platform.</p><p><strong><a href=\"http://socialblood.org/\">Socialblood</a> </strong>is building the largest network of blood donors, hospitals, and blood banks on the internet. Since joining the Free Basics Platform, Socialblood has seen an 85% increase in monthly visitors, a 59% increase in requests for blood, and a 65% decrease in donor response time. Through Free Basics, Socialblood has connected thousands of patients across the globe to life saving blood products.</p><p><strong><a href=\"http://www.maya.com.bd/\">Maya</a></strong>, a women\'s health support website, sees 71% of their traffic from Free Basics. Maya receives 18x more daily queries since launching with Free Basics.</p><p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><strong><a href=\"http://www.1doc3.com/\">1doc3</a></strong>, a digital platform from Colombia that helps real doctors answer medical questions, has seen 21% of total traffic generated from Free Basics. Free Basics has also allowed the company to reach 4 new markets.</span></p><p><strong><a href=\"http://www.babycenter.com/\">BabyCenter</a> </strong>and<strong> <a href=\"http://www.mobilemamaalliance.org/\">MAMA</a></strong> have reached 3.4 million people with vital health information for pregnancy and parenting through Free Basics alone.</p><h3>Join the Free Basics Platform</h3><p><a href=\"http://internetorg.jam3.net/en/contact-us/contact-free-basic-services/\">Contact us</a></p>','Free Basics Platform','','inherit','closed','closed','','25-autosave-v1','','','2015-11-05 03:40:21','2015-11-05 03:40:21','',25,'http://vip.local/en/blog/2015/10/29/25-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1627,1,'2015-10-29 05:06:42','2015-10-29 05:06:42','','2-mission-altJS_20141220_7229','','inherit','open','closed','','2-mission-altjs_20141220_7229','','','2015-10-29 05:06:42','2015-10-29 05:06:42','',0,'http://vip.local/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/2-mission-altJS_20141220_7229.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1628,1,'2015-10-29 05:06:44','2015-10-29 05:06:44','','3-approach-194281_12_iORG_bolivisa1643_R1','','inherit','open','closed','','3-approach-194281_12_iorg_bolivisa1643_r1','','','2015-11-02 22:11:59','2015-11-02 22:11:59','',1748,'http://vip.local/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/3-approach-194281_12_iORG_bolivisa1643_R1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1629,1,'2015-10-29 05:06:45','2015-10-29 05:06:45','','JS_20141214_5971-960x640','','inherit','open','closed','','js_20141214_5971-960x640','','','2015-11-02 22:07:36','2015-11-02 22:07:36','',13,'http://vip.local/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/JS_20141214_5971-960x640.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1630,1,'2015-10-29 05:06:46','2015-10-29 05:06:46','','TBD-Panel-Image','','inherit','open','closed','','tbd-panel-image','','','2015-10-29 05:34:51','2015-10-29 05:34:51','',21,'http://vip.local/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/TBD-Panel-Image.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1631,1,'2015-11-03 02:13:20','2015-11-03 02:13:20','<p>Free Basics is available in 29 countries with the following mobile operators:</p><h4>Africa</h4><ul><li>Angola (Movicel)</li><li>Democratic Republic of the Congo (Tigo)</li><li>Egypt (Etisalat)</li><li>Ghana (Airtel)</li><li>Kenya (Airtel)</li><li>Liberia (Cellcom)</li><li>Malawi (Airtel &amp; TNM)</li><li>Mozambique (Mcel)</li><li>Rwanda (Airtel)</li><li>Senegal (Tigo)</li><li>Seychelles (Airtel) </li><li>South Africa (Cell C)</li><li>Tanzania (Tigo)</li><li>Zambia (Airtel)</li></ul><h4>Asia</h4><ul><li>Bangladesh (Robi)</li><li>Cambodia (Smart Axiata)</li><li>India (Reliance)</li><li>Indonesia (Indosat)</li><li>Maldives (Ooredoo)</li><li>Mongolia (Mobicom) </li><li>Pakistan (Telenor)</li><li>Philippines (Globe &amp; Smart)</li><li>Thailand (TrueMove)</li><li>Timor-Leste (Telkomcel) </li></ul><h4>Latin America</h4><ul><li>Bolivia (Viva)</li><li>Colombia (Tigo)</li><li>Guatemala (Tigo)</li><li>Panama (Digicel)</li><li>Peru (Entel)</li></ul><p>Free Basics will continue to expand to more countries around the world.</p>','Where we\'ve launched','','inherit','closed','closed','','1434-autosave-v1','','','2015-11-03 02:13:20','2015-11-03 02:13:20','',1434,'http://vip.local/en/blog/2015/10/29/1434-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1632,1,'2015-11-03 02:01:15','2015-11-03 02:01:15','<p>Free Basics by Facebook provides people with access to useful websites on their mobile phones in markets where internet access may be less affordable. The websites are available for free without data charges, and include content on things like news, employment, health, education and local information. By introducing people to the benefits of the internet through these websites, we hope to bring more people online and help improve their lives.</p><p><a href=\"/story/where-weve-launched/\">View where Free Basics is available</a></p><h3><strong>Mobile Operators</strong></h3><p>Over 85% of the world\'s population lives in areas with existing cellular coverage, but mobile data is expensive and hard for people to justify when they haven\'t experienced the benefits of the internet. By partnering with mobile operators, over 1 billion people can now experience the knowledge and inspiration that comes from access to basic websites, for free.</p><p>If you are a mobile operator, partner with us to connect the unconnected.</p><p>[io-custom-link css_class=\"link\" source=\"26\" link_text=\"Learn more\"]  </p><p> </p><p><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-1633\" src=\"http://vip.local/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/fbs-made-more-efficient-SHOT_01_06361-300x200.jpg\" alt=\"fbs-made-more-efficient-SHOT_01_06361\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" /></p><h3>Platform</h3><p>In collaboration with hundreds of developers, non-profits, and governments, Free Basics offers access to basic websites for local audiences. If you are a developer, non-profit, or government that aims to reach unconnected populations with your information and services, join the Free Basics Platform.</p><p>[io-custom-link link_src=\"internal\" external_url=\"https://developers.facebook.com/docs/internet-org\" source=\"25\" link_text=\"Learn more\"]</p>','Free Basics by Facebook','','inherit','closed','closed','','20-autosave-v1','','','2015-11-03 02:01:15','2015-11-03 02:01:15','',20,'http://vip.local/en/blog/2015/10/29/20-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1633,1,'2015-10-29 05:18:15','2015-10-29 05:18:15','','fbs-made-more-efficient-SHOT_01_06361','','inherit','open','closed','','fbs-made-more-efficient-shot_01_06361','','','2015-10-29 05:34:12','2015-10-29 05:34:12','',20,'http://vip.local/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/fbs-made-more-efficient-SHOT_